snippet.textDisplay:
Hey guys @ hot ones! There’s an iconic wing joint in Portland, OR called Fire on the Mountain, I worked there for years. Their hottest wing sauce is called the “El Jefe” (means The Boss in Spanish) and I’m not even playing or exaggerating when i say this.. OK, I love spicy food; This sauce is what I’d imagine the lava lakes in hell are made of. The cooks have to wear hazmat suits when they blend it up in the back (El Jefe not only contains every hot pepper imaginable but also a considerable amount of capsaicin oil [ pepper spray]) .
Not even joking, i saw a frat dude, we’ll call him Chad, try to complete the hot wing challenge (eating 12 wings doused in Jefe in under 3 minutes with one napkin, no water, no ranch etc.) ... 30 seconds in, Chad grabs his napkin after standing up and taking off his shirt yelling profanities and trying to stay tough but clearly crying.. anyways, takes his napkin to dab his tear-drenched eyes and, yes, you guessed it.. the napkin was covered in this hot sauce from hell. As I’m sure you can tell where this is going, the story comes to a close; Chad gets Jefe in his eyes which is basically the equivalent of mace to the face, and at this point all hell and comedy broke loose ( I was the lucky server who got to time Chad in this glorious attempted feat) of course, just to show his whole table of college co-Ed’s that he was in fact, a Demi-god whom they should all bow to. Keep in mind, he has already taken his shirt off, screamed at the top of his lungs with tears streaming down his face (which was turning more sweaty, red and veinous by the second) and now.. he has El Jefe sauce in and around his eyeballs.
Chaos ensued; Chad is wedged between three cute ladies on a bench seat against the wall, like a caged Gorilla, who is throwing his title of the Silverback (Alpha, for all you kids out there who don’t watch enough Planet Earth) out the window. Chad attempts to flip the table, its bolted to the floor. Chad screams that he’s going blind, then proceeds to climb over his entire table because the ladies he was surrounded by don’t understand the language of ‘Herramienta de Morir’ (dying tool) and cant get out of Chads way fast enough; Chad only ate two of the twelve wings. Being the supportive person I am, as I stood there watching him attempt to prove his immortality I was cheering him on with the stop watch in hand, knowing full well that not only was he going to fail his mission but I told him it was NOT WORTH IT in the first place because (which I’m sure made him want to do it with more inspo) if you do complete the Jefe challenge, you don’t get your meal for free and one of your lovely servers will approach you post achievement, as your crying and clearly in pain, with a giant chicken wing hat and a Polaroid camera; winners get their picture taken while wearing a chicken wing hat, with a facial expression that says “kill me now please” posted on the wall. So worth it, anyways!...
Chad’s screaming, shirtless, crying, speaking a foreign language derived from excruciating pain, then proceeds to sprint out of the restaurant and down the street (out-run the pain, ya know?) STILL SCREAMING. He left the whole establishment in pure disbelief, and I’m sure well entertained, as I get back to work cackling like a wicked witch who just watched a man hex himself even after being warned of the danger. Chad never returned.. legend has it, the experience left him with no prior memory of the Chad he had been and the dreams he had yet to achieve, and is now living in a van down by the river.
This is a long story but it needed to be told; the dangers of hot sauce are real and this being said.. To you guys @FirstWeFeast #HotOnes check out this El Jefe sauce, it belongs on your show.
